original: Linde, Gunnar Axelsson, distrikts-lantmätare, kapten, Lidköping, f. 13/ 5/84 i Hällestad, Älvsb. 1., av komm:-lantmät. Axel L. o. Hulda Frigell. G. 10 m. Ingrid Maria Tibell. Barn: Lullu f. 11, Kerstin 13, Per-Gunnar 18, Bengt 19. — Mog:ex. 04, reservoff:-ex. 06, lantmät:ex. 09, ex. i geodesi o. astronomi 11, kulturtekn. ex. 12. Lant-mät :auskultant 09-20, tf. byrådir. i lantmät :styr. o. överlantmät. i Skarab. o, Gotl. län m. m., distr :lantmät. i Vara distr. sed. 20. Und:löjtn. i Älvsb. reg. res. 06, löjtn. 17, numera kapt. Ordf. i Lidköp. automobilklubb. Skr.: Flor an inom Leckö eller Sika-jocki slottsområde (39). Hobby: fjä-rilsaml. RVO, statl. h. utm:t. i guld i skytte.
translated: Linde, Gunnar Axelsson, district surveyor, captain, Lidköping, b. 13/5/84 in Hällestad, Älvsborg County, son of municipal surveyor Axel L. and Hulda Frigell. Married on 10 May Ingrid Maria Tibell. Children: Lullu b. 1911, Kerstin b. 1913, Per-Gunnar b. 1898, Bengt b. 1899. Obtained a degree in agriculture in 1904, reserve officer degree in 1906, surveyor degree in 1909, degree in geodesy and astronomy in 1911, and degree in cultural technology in 1912. Worked as an assistant surveyor from 1909 to 1920, acting director of the land surveying board and senior surveyor in Skaraborg and Gotland counties, etc., district surveyor in Vara district since 1920. Second lieutenant in Älvsborg regiment since 1906, lieutenant since 1917, currently captain. Chairman of the Lidköping Automobile Club. Wrote the book "Flora within the Leckö or Sika-jocki castle area" (1939). Hobby: butterfly collection. Received the Royal Order of Vasa, gold medal in marksmanship.
